Description: SoftEther VPN client (Cedar protocol over TLS)
 A minimal SoftEther VPN client that speaks the Cedar wire protocol
 directly over TLS.  Provides:
 .
   * easy_se_cli — a CLI/daemon that opens a TUN device, runs DHCP over
     the SoftEther Ethernet tunnel, and forwards packets between the
     kernel and the server.
   * A systemd template unit (easy-se@.service) so one instance per
     VPN profile can be enabled with systemctl enable easy-se@<name>.
   * KEY=VALUE config files in /etc/easy-se/<profile>.conf compatible
     with systemd EnvironmentFile=.
 .
 TLS server-certificate validation is enabled by default; the binary
 uses the system CA store via /etc/ssl/certs.
